Models are always going to change - there's always a lot up in the air and new information comes in every day. BUT, I know that a lot of other epidemiologists and projectionists (projectioners?) have mentioned that the IMHE isn't the most reliable model compared to what other institutions are doing.

&#x200B;

I think it's tough to really talk about America as a whole unit, too, because we're so large and the population is so spread out that each state is kind of on its own separate curve. Some states are going to be a lot closer to a major slowdown in cases than others.

